  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, curry powder, garlic powder, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the cubed shortening and use a pastry blender or your fingers to work it into the flour mixture until it resembles coarse crumbs.",
    "Stir in the chopped tarragon and diced Scotch bonnet peppers.",
    "Press the mixture into the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish.",
    "In a separate bowl, whisk together the egg yolk and a little water.",
    "Brush the egg wash over the crust to glaze it.",
    "Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and set."
  ],
